<div id="articles">

<div class="article" id="art1">
<span class="sd-info-block" style="display: none">
	<span class="sd-key-sid">08/12/23/184257</span>
	<span class="type">story</span>
	
</span>



<div class="generaltitle" >
	<div class="title">
		<h3 >
			Your Favorite Tech / Eng. / CS Books?
			
		</h3>
	</div>
</div>
	<div class="details"><small>

	
	Posted by
	
	<a href="http://twitter.com/kdawson">kdawson</a>

	on Tue Dec 23, 2008 01:35 PM<br>
	from the art-of-computer-programming dept.
	</small></div>
	<div class="body">
		<div class="topic">
		
		
		
			<a href="//news.slashdot.org/search.pl?tid=172">
				<img src="//a.fsdn.com/sd/topics/topicbooks.gif" width="63" height="38" alt="Books" title="Books" >
			</a>
		
		
			
			
			
			
				
					<a href="//news.slashdot.org/search.pl?tid=513" class="topic2">
						<img src="//a.fsdn.com/sd/topics/topicmediaall.gif" width="73" height="59" alt="Media" title="Media" >
					</a>
				
		
			
			
			
				
		
			
			
			
				
		
		
		</div>
		<div class="intro">
			<a href="mailto:slashdot@chriseineke.com" rel="nofollow">chris_eineke</a> writes <i>"I like to read and to collect good books related to computer science. I'm talking about stuff like the classic textbooks (<a href="http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_ss_gw_0_5?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=introduction+to+algorithms&amp;x=0&amp;y=0&amp;sprefix=Intro">Introduction to Algorithms 2nd ed.</a>, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_ss_gw?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Tanenbaum&amp;x=0&amp;y=0">Tanenbaum's Operating Systems</a> series) and practitioners' books (<a href="http://www.amazon.com/Practice-Programming-Addison-Wesley-Professional-Computing/dp/020161586X/ref=pd_bbs_sr_1?ie=UTF8&amp;s=books&amp;qid=1230050741&amp;sr=8-1">The Practice of Programming</a>, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Code-Complete-Practical-Handbook-Construction/dp/0735619670/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;s=books&amp;qid=1230050768&amp;sr=1-1">Code Complete</a>) and all-around excellent books (<a href="http://www.amazon.com/Structure-Interpretation-Computer-Programs-Engineering/dp/0262011530/ref=sr_1_1_s9_rk?ie=UTF8&amp;s=books&amp;s9r=8a5850a41a9c975a011b7c708d8b1904&amp;itemPosition=1&amp;qid=1230050803&amp;sr=1-1">Structure and Interpretation of Computer Programs</a>, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Practical-Common-Lisp-Peter-Seibel/dp/1590592395/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;s=books&amp;qid=1230050827&amp;sr=1-1">Practical Common Lisp</a>). What's your stocking-stuffer book this Christmas? What books have been sitting on your shelves that you think are the best ones of their kind? Which ones do you think are -1 Overrated? (All links are referral-free.)"</i>
		</div>





		







	</div>
	<div class="tags"><span id="updown-" class="vote">
	<a href="//news.slashdot.org/faq/UI.shtml#ui700" onclick="return false" class="up" title="Vote this item up">+</a>
	<a href="//news.slashdot.org/faq/UI.shtml#ui700" onclick="return false" class="down" title="Vote this item down">-</a>
</span></div>

