	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_26215691"><p> <a href="http://www.borders.com/online/store/TitleDetail?sku=0300084730" title="borders.com">The Computer and the Brain</a> [borders.com].</p><p>There is no book that says more what computing is all about, from the historical perspective of appreciating how genius the founders of computer science were to the zen of how digital computers actually operate and to a different perspective on analog computing.</p><p>This book is only 110 pages and is 50 years old, but it is still worth more than any other book mentioned.</p></div>
